Bucket grouping is a feature that allows Discord to efficiently group server members into smaller chunks of data. This feature is useful for operations that require access to multiple server members, such as sending mass invitations or querying a list of members for a given role. The grouping is done based on the presence data and member data of each server member, which is stored in Redis, a distributed in-memory \_{"Redis", "in-memory databases Choice 1"}\_key-value data structure.

